# AI Agent & Automation Projects - Development Rules

## Project Context
This folder contains 15 intelligent agents for workflow automation, productivity enhancement, and autonomous task execution.

## Technology Stack
- **AI/ML**: OpenAI GPT-4, Anthropic Claude, LangChain, LlamaIndex
- **Agent Frameworks**: AutoGPT, BabyAGI, CrewAI, Semantic Kernel
- **Automation**: n8n, Zapier API, Make (Integromat)
- **Backend**: Node.js, Python (FastAPI, Django)
- **Task Queues**: Bull, Celery, RabbitMQ, Redis
- **Databases**: PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Vector DBs (Pinecone, Weaviate, Chroma)
- **Orchestration**: Temporal, Apache Airflow

## Development Guidelines

### Code Standards
- Implement robust error handling and retry logic
- Use async/await for all I/O operations
- Write modular, composable agent components
- Implement proper logging and monitoring
- Use type hints/TypeScript for better maintainability

### AI Agent Architecture
```
Agent = Perception → Reasoning → Planning → Action → Learning
```

### Agent Design Patterns
- **ReAct Pattern**: Reasoning + Acting in interleaved manner
- **Chain-of-Thought**: Break complex tasks into steps
- **Tool Use**: Agents with access to external tools/APIs
- **Multi-Agent**: Collaborative agents with specialized roles
- **Memory Systems**: Short-term and long-term memory

### Project Structure
```
project-name/
├── src/
│   ├── agents/         # Agent implementations
│   ├── tools/          # Tools/functions agents can use
│   ├── memory/         # Memory systems
│   ├── prompts/        # Prompt templates
│   ├── workflows/      # Workflow definitions
│   ├── services/       # External integrations
│   ├── utils/          # Helper functions
│   └── config/         # Configuration
├── tests/              # Test files
├── logs/               # Log files
└── package.json
```

### Agent Development Best Practices
- Define clear agent objectives and constraints
- Implement proper task decomposition
- Use structured outputs (JSON, schemas)
- Implement human-in-the-loop for critical decisions
- Monitor agent behavior and costs
- Implement safety guardrails
- Version control prompts and configurations

### Memory Management
- **Short-term Memory**: Current conversation/task context
- **Long-term Memory**: Vector database for retrieval
- **Episodic Memory**: Past experiences and outcomes
- **Semantic Memory**: General knowledge and facts
- Implement memory pruning and summarization

### Tool Integration
- Define clear tool interfaces and schemas
- Implement proper error handling for tool failures
- Validate tool inputs and outputs
- Monitor tool usage and performance
- Implement tool access controls

### Workflow Orchestration
- Break complex tasks into manageable steps
- Implement proper state management
- Handle failures and retries gracefully
- Support parallel and sequential execution
- Implement checkpointing for long-running tasks

### Testing Requirements
- Unit test individual agent components
- Integration test agent workflows
- Test with various input scenarios
- Mock external API calls
- Test error handling and edge cases
- Measure agent performance and accuracy

### Performance Optimization
- Implement caching for repeated queries
- Use streaming for long responses
- Optimize prompt length and token usage
- Batch similar operations
- Monitor and optimize API costs
- Implement rate limiting

### Security Considerations
- Validate all agent inputs and outputs
- Implement proper authentication for agent actions
- Sandbox agent execution environments
- Monitor for prompt injection attacks
- Implement audit logging for agent actions
- Set resource limits and timeouts

### Monitoring & Observability
- Log all agent decisions and actions
- Track token usage and costs
- Monitor success/failure rates
- Implement alerting for anomalies
- Track task completion times
- Measure user satisfaction

